data.title: Latitude Festival
data.meta_description: Alt-J, Portishead, Noel Gallagher’s High Flying Birds, Manic Street Preachers, Caribou, James Blake, Laura Marling, Wild Beasts, Jon Hopkins, The Vaccines, SBTR
data.text:
Alt-J, Portishead, Noel Gallagher’s High Flying Birds, Manic Street Preachers, Caribou, James Blake, Laura Marling, Wild Beasts, Jon Hopkins, The Vaccines, SBTRKT, La Roux, Public Service Broadcasting, Savages, Sun Kil Moon, Warpaint + more.

Celebrating its tenth year in 2015, Latitude is among the most successful of the new generation of festivals thanks to its fairytale setting of forest, lake and meadow and its generally adventurous pop and alt rock line-up (this year boasting an appearance by Bristol trip hop kings Portishead, among others). Latitude is also special for its laid back, family-friendly atmosphere and its choice of arts that takes in comedy, poetry and theatre as well as a literary salon. As the name would suggest, this is one of the most broad-minded music festivals around.
